The paper deals with the problem of detecting fingerprint spoof attacks using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning algorithms for this purpose also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the collection and analysis of large datasets, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
